# Documentation

- Update relevant docs when making architectural, operational, or reliability changes.
- Prefer editing canonical docs over duplicating guidance in chat or one-off notes.
- Clearly label **facts** (verified in repo/runtime), **assumptions**, and **recommendations**.
- Do not document aspirational features as shipped.
- Keep runbooks and ADRs aligned with what operators can actually do today.
